In [17]:
def f(mu, sigma, x):
    return 1/(np.sqrt(2*np.pi)*sigma) * np.exp(-(x-mu)**2/(2*sigma**2))

t = np.arange(-5, 5, 0.1)

plt.figure() # optional

plt.subplot(211)
plt.plot(t, f(0, 1, t), 'ro', t, f(0, 2, t), 'k')

plt.subplot(212)
plt.plot(t, f(-1, 1, t), 'b--')
Out[17]:
[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x7fb5ef54ca90>]

In [19]:
def normal(mu, sigma, n=100):
    return mu + sigma * np.random.randn(n)
plt.hist(normal(0, 1, 1000), 50, density=10, alpha=0.95)
plt.axis([-3, 3, 0, 0.5])
plt.grid(True)

In [25]:
grayScaleArray = imgArray.size*[0]
weight = [0.299, 0.587, 0.114]
for i in range(imgArray.shape[0]):
    for j in range(imgArray.shape[1]):
        grayValue = 0
        for k in range(imgArray.shape[2]):
            grayValue += imgArray[i, j, k]*weight[k]
            grayScaleArray[i*imgArray.shape[1] + j] = grayValue

In [36]:
file = open("./epoch.txt", mode='r')
data = file.readlines()
trainAccuracy = []
testAccuracy = []
trainLoss = []
testLoss = []
for line in data:
    line = line.split('\t')
    line.remove('\n')
    line = list(map(float, line))
    trainAccuracy.append(line[1])
    testAccuracy.append(line[3])
    trainLoss.append(line[0])
    testLoss.append(line[2])
